    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Windows</title>
        <para>The standard passenger windows are an aluminum extruded window assembly. The windows are equipped with a
            positive latch drop down type upper window section. Slide latch mechanisms are located at the upper corners
            of each window assembly to lock the window in the desired position. The window assemblies are completely
            removable for serviceability, from the bus interior.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700568" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g4700568.webp" filename="../figg47/G4700568.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 68. Standard Passenger Windows</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">TOP WINDOW LOCKING LATCH</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">WINDOW POST COVER PLATE</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EMERGENCY WINDOW LOCKING LATCH</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">WINDOW LOWER GLASS PANEL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Passenger windows are sealed thermal glass panels that are easily serviced if damaged.</para>
        <figure id="f4700569" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g4700569.webp" filename="../figg47/G4700569.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 69. Emergency Exit Push Out Windows</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">WINDOW LATCHES</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">UPPER WINDOW PANE (WINDOW AND FRAME SLIDES UP AND DOWN)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">WINDOW TRIM COVER PLATES</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">STATIONARY WINDOW PANE (LOWER)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EMERGENCY WINDOW RELEASE LATCH</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>The bus body is equipped with emergency exit windows and doors. Opening an emergency window or door will
            activate an alarm or buzzer (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700570">Fig. 70, Item 4</hotlnk>) at the driver's position when the key is in the on or
            accessory position. Depending on the local requirements the emergency window will unlatch and push out and
            is either vertically or horizontally hinged.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700570" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g4700570.webp" filename="../figg47/G4700570.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 70. Emergency Window Open - Relay Switch</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">WINDOW SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EMERGENCY WINDOW EXIT LATCH</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EMERGENCY WINDOW EXIT CLIP</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EMERGENCY WINDOW AJAR WARNING SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">LOWER WINDOW SILL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
